              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/83863174-literary-redhead?shelf=featured-netgalley-review">featured-netgalley-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/83863174-literary-redhead?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/83863174-literary-redhead?shelf=autobiography-biography-memoir">autobiography-biography-memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/83863174-literary-redhead?shelf=humor">humor</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2841958865" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5719527291069411013">Purportedly the memoirs of two 20th Century English spies involving a certain London gentlemen’s club. Veddy British, very non-PC, very absurdist humor. A wildly amusing cup of comedic tea! 4 of 5 stars<br/><br/>Thanks to the author, publisher and NetGalley for the ARC. Opinions are mine. Pub Date 01 Jul 2018. #Scoundrels #NetGalley</span>

          </span>
        </div>


