  <span id="freeText7263283977436896707" style="display:none">I have been searching for a book deserving of a search entitled "like flashman" for a number of years. I've tried many, but none have delivered tales of bravado, idiocy and historical information until Scoundrels. Both characters are engaging and hilariously un-P.C - perfect.<br /><br />If there was one thing I would change - I would double the length of this book with more stories. I can't wait for volume two. I read this in 2 days, on day 2 I cancelled a date, cracked a decent bottle of 2015 Argentinian Malbec, and thoroughly enjoyed finishing reading a book that will be in my top two for 2017.<br /><br />I can recommend Stewart Hennessey's Comrade Fox if anybody would like a similar type of adventure.<br /><br /></span>
