<div id="review_2257307521" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2257307521" />
    <a title="Tom" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8968920-tom"><img alt="Tom" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1417121486p2/8968920.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2257307521?book_show_action=true">Jan 14, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tom" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tom" href="/user/show/8968920-tom">Tom</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2257307521" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15853856141144876531">I laughed all the way through at this. Very British sitcom classic type humour with lots of history in-jokes. I particularly liked the exotic named cigarette brands. I would have given it 5 stars except the gross out level the humour occasionally reaches will not be for everyone.</span>

          </span>
